<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Harwill year shr slips as economy slows.</title>
<headline>Harwill year shr slips as economy slows.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended June 30, 1996</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     15.0	  vs 15.4</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 7.5	   vs same</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   2.95	  vs 3.05</p>
<p>    Tax			 1.01	  vs 1.36</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   0.90	  vs 0.49</p>
<p>    Turnover		  39.2	  vs 48.08</p>
<p>    Net asset value/shr (cts) 147     vs 142</p>
<p>Div payable October 18</p>
<p>on register October 4</p>
<p>Full name: Harwill Investments Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Investment group Harwill said that its results had been hit by the slowdown of the South African economy during the second half of the year.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
